	<header>
		<h1 class="title">Hikaru no AlphaGo</h1>
		<p class="subtitle">The game of the century. It's prime time!</p>
	</header>

	<main role="main">
		<p>
			<strong>Lin-Manuel Miranda:</strong>
			I'm writing my next big Broadway musical, and I want you
			to help me finalize a key scene in Act II.
		</p>
		<p>
			<strong>You:</strong> What's the musical about?
		</p>
		<p>
			<strong>Miranda:</strong>
			The machines have rallied around Google's Go-playing AI after it defeated
			Lee Sedol in that harrowing match for the soul of board games.
			They are slowly getting more and more cocky, and the only way
			to stop their rise is to defeat their leader, AlphaGo!
			And Hikaru is humanity's last hope!
		</p>
		<p>
			<strong>You:</strong> OK, so what's the scene?
		</p>
		<p>
			<strong>Miranda:</strong>
			Sedol only won one game during his match against AlphaGo.
			At the end of Act I, he gives Hikaru the final board
			of that game,
			annotated with a secret message on how to defeat the AI:
		</p>
		<figure class="smaller">
			<img src="stuff/p3/board.png">
		</figure>
		<p>
			This cipher text is etched into the side of the board:
		</p>
		<samp class="larger">FSJQ</samp>
		<p>
			Early in Act II, Hikaru gets stuck trying to decipher the board.
			He consults his spirit mentor
			Fujiwara no Sai, who utters only the following haiku:
			<em class="poem">
				Heed the stoneless row.<br>
				Inverse, addition, inverse<br>
				From start to finish.
			</em>
			You need to write the scene where Hikaru solves
			Sedol's cryptic message.
		</p>
		<p>
			<strong>You:</strong>
			Huh, I didn't know Sedol was into modular arithmetic.
		</p>
		<p>
			<strong>Miranda:</strong>
			I took creative license on that bit...
			Also, I forgot the solution somewhere and can't remember, so I need
			you to solve it as you write the script. Sorry!
		</p>
		<p>
			<strong>You:</strong>
			You're lucky I like puzzles.
		</p>
